Sentencing proceeded.  Statements made as to sentencing.
AS TO COUNT 1:
Court sentenced defendant to serve 120 DAYS in the House of Correction consecutive to any sentence, with credit for 8 days served; Huber privileges for work, medical and treatment.  Court has no objection against electronic monitoring.  

Defendant ordered to pay a fine in the amount of $1,200.00 plus costs, penalties and surcharges or a civil judgment will be entered with tax intercept. Defendant is to pay $25.00 a month starting January 1st, 2023. 

Court ordered defendant's driving privileges revoked for 4 YEARS.  Court orders all vehicles owned by the defendant must be equipped with an ignition interlock device for a period of 4 YEARS.

Drivers Safety Assessment ordered.

Defendant Sylwia Katarzyna Hass in court with attorney Amanda M. Parent.  Brad Alan Vorpahl appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Drug Treatment Court

AS TO COUNTS 2 AND 5:
Parties are prepared to enter into a Deferred Sentencing Agreement.
Defendant was advised of constitution rights and maximum penalties, waived all rights and entered pleas of GUILTY.  Defendant examined as to the plea.  Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights, Addendum and Elements/Jury Instructions, received and filed.  Stipulation by parties to complaint as a factual basis to sustain the guilty plea.  Defendant further advised that if he is not a US citizen deportation is possible.  Court found the defendant guilty and entered Judgment of Conviction as charged in the Information.  Defendant enters into Drug Treatment Court (DTC) with the sentencing deferred.  Deferred Sentencing Agreement received and filed.  

AS TO COUNTS 3 AND 4:
Pursuant to negotiations and on the Motion of the State, Court Ordered Counts 3 and 4 DISMISSED BUT READ IN for the purpose of sentencing.

AS TO COUNT 1:
Defendant changes plea to GUILTY. Defendant examined as to plea, advised of Constitutional Rights and the maximum penalties. Defendant further advised that if not a US citizen, deportation is possible. Court found that the defendant knowingly, voluntarily and intelligently waived rights.  Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights form, Addendum, and Elements/Jury Instructions received and filed. Parties stipulate to the Criminal Complaint as a factual basis to sustain defendant's plea.  Court found defendant GUILTY and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record.  

Court ordered case adjourned for review hearing in Branch 17.
